 means ‘John's settlement’, from the genitive case of the Middle English personal name <i>Johan</i>, <i>Jon</i> (see   John  ) + Middle English <i>ton</i> ‘town, village, settlement’.","History: As far as can be ascertained, most Scottish bearers of this surname are descendants of John, probably a Norman baron from England, who held lands at Johnstone in Annandale from the Bruce family in the late 12th century. His son Gilbert was the first to take the surname Johnstone and their descendants later held the earldom of Annandale."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir John Johnstone had at least 1 son. He died after 1296, in Dumfriesshire, Scotland."},"et":{"–after 1296":"–pärast 1296","–1309":"–1309","–1296":"–1296","1296":"1296","after 1296":"pärast 1296","1309":"1309","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"–after 1296":"–1296 jälkeen","–1309":"–1309","–1296":"–1296","1296":"1296","after 1296":"1296 jälkeen","1309":"1309","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"–after 1296":"–après 1296","–1309":"–1309","–1296":"–1296","1296":"1296","after 1296":"après 1296","1309":"1309","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Sir John Johnstone a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé après 1296, à Dumfriesshire, Écosse."},"de":{"–after 1296":"–nach 1296","–1309":"–1309","–1296":"–1296","1296":"1296","after 1296":"nach 1296","1309":"1309","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Sir John Johnstone hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb nach 1296 in Dumfriesshire, Scotland."},"ht":{"–after 1296":"–after 1296","–1309":"–1309","–1296"